The paper deals with incremental computation and derivatives of fixpoints, which are concepts commonly studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also specifically mentions the application of these concepts to generalised Datalog programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper discusses the algebraic properties of change actions, which is a topic that can be related to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
